Following the conventional SMD approach25, the truncated ribosome was split into three regions. Bases and residues containing one or more atoms within 28 Å of ERY comprised the dynamic region. The buffer region is between 28 and 34 Å, while the remaining portion belongs to the outer region. Atoms within the dynamic region were not subject to any restraints during the SMD simulation course, but harmonic restraints were applied to non-hydrogen atoms within the buffer and outer regions with spring constants of 5 and 10 kcal mol−1 Å−2, respectively. The ribosomes were solvated in a rectangular box with distances between the system and box edge of 12 Å, 12 Å and 28 Å along the \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
